Operator Control Services (CControl) - Database Migrations

Migration files for ccontrol schema updates.

Naming Convention
-----------------
NNN_description.sql

Examples:
  001_add_gline_column.sql
  002_add_index_on_servers.sql
  003_alter_bans_table.sql


Example Migration File
----------------------
ALTER TABLE glines ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS updated_at TIMESTAMP;
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_glines_updated_at ON glines(updated_at);


Checking Applied Migrations
----------------------------
To see which migrations have been applied to the ccontrol database:

  psql ccontrol -c "SELECT file FROM gnuworld_migrations WHERE module='ccontrol' ORDER BY applied_at;"


Automatic Migration Application
--------------------------------
Migrations are applied automatically when ccontrol starts. Simply:

  1. Place your migration file in this directory
  2. Restart gnuworld
  3. The migration will be automatically detected and applied

The migration system will log each migration as it's applied.
If a migration fails, gnuworld will exit with an error message.


For detailed documentation, see ../../doc/README.migrations
